# Phase 9: Typography and Color Picker Enhancements Completed

## What Was Achieved

I have fully implemented the requested enhancements for Phase 9, completely modernizing how typography and color settings are applied in KeryxPro's Presentation Settings.

### 1. Refined Color Pickers
All color picker boxes (background colors and typography colors) have been visually updated from a small square to a more distinguishable, horizontally rectangular shape with slight rounded corners. This eliminates any confusion with the standard checkboxes next to them.

### 2. New Typography Dialog
The old placeholder Input Decorators have been replaced with dynamic, clickable boxes that clearly show the currently selected font family and size (e.g., "Arial 20").

Clicking on this box now opens a comprehensive `Typography` popup containing:
- **Font Family:** A searchable dropdown containing a predefined list of 22 standard and common system fonts (Arial, Tahoma, Verdana, Times New Roman, Calibri, etc.).
- **Font Size:** A searchable dropdown allowing sizes from 5 to 100.
- **Font Color:** A rectangular color picker box.
- **Underline:** A checkbox toggle.
- **Fill (Text Background):** A checkbox toggle coupled with a color picker to set text highlights/backgrounds.
- **Stroke (Text Border):** A checkbox toggle coupled with a color picker to set the color of the text outline/stroke. (Currently using a standard stroke thickness of 2.0).

> [!TIP]
> **Independent Settings:** All these settings apply completely independently for both the Title and the Body, and are cleanly separated between Song presets and Scripture presets.

### 3. Database Updates
I added all the necessary properties (`Underline`, `HasFill`, `FillColor`, `HasStroke`, `StrokeColor`) to the underlying `PresentationSettings` database model and successfully regenerated the Isar code to handle the schema migration cleanly.

### 4. Real-time Preview Integration
I updated the presentation preview screen to instantly reflect these new typography settings without touching your saved presets. If you tweak the stroke, fill, underline, or font family, the central preview automatically updates. These settings are only formally written to the database when you click the "Save Settings" button, preserving the previous non-destructive workflow.

